posts.body:
>>9e5bb9a3-ba40-4dfb-a1cb-734df0a4222e
Africa for the Africans
Asia for the Asians
White countries for everybody!

Tell me, what's so bad about the land that your ancestors came from? Why do you hate your people so much that you insist on living with your so-called oppressors? If you wanted to leave, you do realize that literally no one would try to stop you? That there would be no one with guns threatening your life? Why do your people get their own space, but mine don't? Why do you think it's okay to force us to live by your rules in our own land?

>>952df5d7-72d6-4b4b-ac4c-2e06172b2c5f
Reminder that Jim said the El Paso manifesto was posted on Instagram first, then later uploaded to 8chan...

https://youtu.be/yKPdbEAmWGE?t=239

>>60b74058-03ff-41ff-91bc-a57cde30a342
>we cannot even reach old 8ch userbase to tell about bunker
We're trickling in.

>>d4961e29-0875-41e3-a993-bca6e47b2fe0
>It feels like this is the secrecy we needed.
If you think ZeroNet affords secrecy, you're gravely mistaken and risking the safety of technologically inept anons by suggesting that it does. It's even more imperative here to shield your IP than it would be on clearnet chans. Peer 2 Peer is great, but trackers sharing your IP is how ZeroNet functions. I've been screwing around on here for years and I promise you that there were already plenty of anarchists, Marxists, and mentally unstable types present. More will come, in pursuit of us. They're probably already maintaining a table of IPs that seed the zite. Prepare accordingly.

>>193fa5bc-d367-45a3-ae9c-4816e83e1c86
>Using a bunch of shill to promote the manifesto 
You actually think reposting the manifesto was a clever plot to get 8ch taken down...? Seriously? The chans existed long before Qanon was ever a thing. The majority of us have nothing to do with that stuff. EVERY manifesto gets circulated on the chans and especially pol. Even manifestos from shootings in European countries. The whole reason Qtards found their way to the chans in the first place was because, just like the rest of us, you were seeking some form of forbidden knowledge or obscure fellowship. Well guess what? Manifestos are forbidden knowledge too and we have a voracious curiosity.

>>2fbdc91e-2068-43cb-8d63-66e487ce2241
>but good luck trying to take this offline.
ZeroNet is decentralized. It unfortunately relies on trackers for peering... Meaning that until we get a configuration that implements a DHT for the site, or ZeroNet-proper finally implements the feature for the entire network, there's still realistic potential for them to cause intermittent disruptions.

>>71e58dea-6778-4211-af88-7c1e3fc2bc7a
>don't you lads think it's more plausible
That's a government employee and it's painfully obvious.
>surely they're not that stupid.
Are you new?

>>c0c38bfa-d92f-4e6c-bb05-4559b9570a2b
Who needs IDs? They already wear neon signs.

>To mute and delete a board from your local machine, click the hash next to the board name.
Do this on the main page. Hopefully in the future the zite owner will implement a feature to make this easier and more organized.
